channel.title: Can't get server online
channel.description:
Hello guys,
I can't get my server online. I'm using uTorrent as portforwarding, because my router doesn't work. I don't know if I've putted my no-ip.biz adress in the correct place, I think that is also a problem.
Can someone help me? (Teamviewer is possible)

item.title: Can't get server online
item.dc:creator: @Mod_Brandon12111 Mod Brandon12111
item.description:
@Mod_Brandon12111 wrote:

Well that’s simple, you don’t change YOUR ip to your no-ip. You keep your Ip as 127.0.0.1 and make a 2nd client (copy of other one) and turn that to the no-ip for the people who download it. Problem #1 Solved.

Read full topic
